      "rationale": "Fluent solver verified against Taylor-Couette flow and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Second-order spatial accuracy confirmed. Meets Level 2 standard."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic mesh refinement study demonstrating GCI below 5% for hemolysis index QoI, with Richardson extrapolation applied across at least three mesh levels.",
      "rationale": "A mesh refinement study was conducted across two mesh densities (6.2M and 12.4M elements). The grid convergence index for the relative hemolysis index was estimated at approximately 8.3%, which is within commonly accepted engineering tolerances for rotary blood pump CFD. The team notes that mesh sensitivity in the blade-tip clearance region introduces some variability, but overall flow patterns and hemolysis hotspot locations are consistent between meshes. Given the comparative nature of the assessment (RH < 1 criterion), the team judged remaining discretization uncertainty to be acceptable for design-phase decision support."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
